From: Kreijstal <kreijstal@hotmail.com>
Subject: encoding_crc32: only include arm64_neon.h on MSVC

arm64_neon.h is an MSVC-only header. clang also defines _M_ARM64 when
targeting aarch64-pc-windows, so the original guard sent the CLANGARM64
build looking for the MSVC header. Restrict the guard to _MSC_VER so
clang falls through to the GNU/clang arm_acle.h.

diff --git a/libretro-common/encodings/encoding_crc32.c b/libretro-common/encodings/encoding_crc32.c
index 26c7fc5..87df0ef 100644
--- a/libretro-common/encodings/encoding_crc32.c
+++ b/libretro-common/encodings/encoding_crc32.c
@@ -27,7 +27,7 @@
 
 #if __ARM_FEATURE_CRC32
 
-#ifdef _M_ARM64
+#if defined(_MSC_VER) && defined(_M_ARM64)
 # include <arm64_neon.h>
 #else
 # include <arm_acle.h>
